litical philosophy, the book highlights how his insights about globalisation and democracy can inform present theoretical debates.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDemocracyxPhilosophy. 0aEthics. 0aGlobalizationxPhilosophy. 0aPolitical science (General). 0aPolitical sciencezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aSociology (General). 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aGreat Society.  aJohn Dewey.  ademocratic socialism.  aglobal democracy.  aglobal equality.  aglobal justice.  aglobal public.  aliberal capitalism.  anational democracy.  apolitical philosophy.  asocial intelligence.1 aNarayan, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/9781526101020zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526101020zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526101020/original  a978-3-11-128282-4 Manchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packageb2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA